      "library": "com.esotericsoftware:kryo-shaded:3.0.3",
      "summary": "Kryo 3.0.3 is self-contained apart from normal transitive dependencies and needs no Docker service, but meaningful native-image-safe serialization tests should disable Kryo's ReflectASM runtime class generation before constructing Kryo.",
      "deterministic_setup": [],
      "agent_guidance": "Before creating any Kryo instance in generated tests, set `com.esotericsoftware.kryo.util.Util.isAndroid = true` to force Kryo's DefaultInstantiatorStrategy onto the reflection path instead of ReflectASM runtime class generation. Also call `kryo.setAsmEnabled(false)` for serializer instances. Use ordinary `Input`/`Output`, POJOs with accessible no-arg constructors, and concrete collections such as `new ArrayList<>(...)`; avoid making `Arrays.asList(...)` itself the deserialization target because Kryo 3 cannot instantiate `java.util.Arrays$ArrayList`.",
      "risks": [
        "The `kryo-shaded` artifact embeds shaded ReflectASM/ASM; if tests exercise the default ReflectASM path, native-image execution can fail with unsupported runtime class definition such as `*ConstructorAccess`.",
        "Setting `Util.isAndroid = true` is a test workaround that avoids covering ReflectASM acceleration, but it enables meaningful coverage of Kryo serialization APIs under Native Image."
